HEADWORD: Spiricle
<hw>Spi"ri*cle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Dim., fr. L.
<ets>spira</ets> a coil.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>One of certain
minute coiled threads in the coating of some seeds. When moistened these
threads protrude in great numbers.</def> <rj><au>Gray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spirifer</ent>⟦br⟧
